<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Cuban Minister</gloss> to
                                Acting Secretary of State <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Cuba</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 201.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to the memorandum of your
                            Department of the 17th of January of this year, and to mine of the 19th
                            of the same month and year, I would like to know if, in view of the
                            urgent condition of Mr. Luciano F. Arestuche, to whom, as a grace, that
                            Department is disposed to grant $500 for injuries suffered at the hands
                            of soldiers of the American Army, it would be possible to deliver to me
                            the said sum to have it reach the said destitute individual.</p>
                        <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales de
                            Quesada.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>